1d:T708,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Katie handle storm damage emergencies?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie identifies storm damage by keywords (leak, water coming through, storm, wind damage) and marks the enquiry as emergency priority. You'll get an immediate WhatsApp with 'STORM DAMAGE — URGENT' in the header. Customers also receive an SMS confirming help is on the way."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can customers send roof photos to Katie?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie invites customers to send photos to a dedicated WhatsApp number. Photos are automatically linked to the enquiry in your dashboard, so you can assess the damage before you even call back."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does AI call handling work for insurance roofing claims?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie specifically asks about insurance status and captures the insurance company name, policy number, and loss adjuster details when available. Insurance work is tagged as 'insurance' in your dashboard for specialised follow-up."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What if I can't get to an emergency call immediately?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Tap 'Call Back' and set an estimated arrival time. Katie sends the customer an SMS: 'Your roofer will call you back within 30 minutes. Emergency priority confirmed.' Most customers appreciate the transparency over silence."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much is a missed roofing job worth?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Emergency tile repairs average £200-400. Full re-roofs are £8,000-25,000. Insurance claims can exceed £50,000. At £59/month, capturing one missed re-roof pays for 10+ years of Whoza."}}]}1e:T53e,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"How to Set Up AI Call Handling for Roofers","description":"Four-step process to get Katie answering calls for your roofer business","totalTime":"PT30M","supply":[{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"UK phone number or existing business line"}],"tool":[{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Smartphone with WhatsApp"}],"step":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Storm hits — phones start ringing","text":"Katie answers every call with your roofing company's greeting. She identifies if it's an active leak, storm damage, or routine maintenance"},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Roof-specific qualification","text":"Captures: roof type (tile, slate, flat, metal), property age, leak location, insurance status, and whether photos are available. Active leaks get emergency priority"},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"WhatsApp with full context","text":"Alert shows: 'Active leak — bedroom ceiling — 1930s semi — tiled roof — insured — photos available — urgent callback' with customer number and photo link"},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Accept emergency or schedule survey","text":"For active leaks: tap to accept and head straight there. For quotes: schedule a roof survey with time preference. Insurance work gets flagged for priority handling"}]}13:[[["$","script","0",{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$1d"}}],["$","script","1",{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$1e"}}],"$L1f","$L20","$L21"],"$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26"]
